Package: shapeindices
Title: Shape Indices for (Multi)Polygons via Constrained Delaunay Triangulation
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R:
    person("Nikhil", "Kaza", , "nkaza@unc.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Computes convexity, moment-of-inertia compactness, moment
    isotropy (elongation), directional balance (angular concentration of
    mass about its own centroid), span (mean-pairwise-distance), radial
    concentration (mean-distance-to-geometric-median), and depth (mean
    distance from interior points to the boundary) indices for
    (multi)polygons using constrained Delaunay triangulation (CDT). In addition, it computes 
    classic boundary/hull/bounding-box compactness scores from the literature (convex-hull ratio, Polsby-Popper,
    width-length ratio, Reock, Detour, Exchange) that need no
    triangulation at all.
    Supports an exact, exhaustive all-pairs method and a Monte Carlo (random-line)
    estimator for large meshes, optional per-triangle or per-sub-polygon
    weighting (e.g. by population), and batch computation over 'sf' data
    frames, including weighted aggregation of a collection of sub-polygons
    into one overall shape.
